save a match and buy a farm
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:a catchprase used as a caution against unnecessary waste; spec. waste of matches. -->ca1920 at least, and fairly general throughout NZ where buying a farm was one of the practicable rural dreams. <i>p.c. W.H. Oliver</i> `More likely to fit with NZ rural ambitions than with English': I.A. Gordon `Not heard in Britain'.
Origin:[none]
